1. Copy the backup files from Production.
    Note: Make sure network firewall has been configured together with passwordless ssh.

    scp @<PROD_SERVER_INTERNAL_IP>:/docker-data/ubuntu/backups/CAPS/backup_20250503_003105.tar.gz /home/ubuntu/CAPS/COPIED_BACKUP/

2. Stop the running containers if any.

    cd <PROJECT_DIRECTORY>
    docker-compose stop

3. restore by running the command below

    tar -xzvf /home/ubuntu/CAPS/COPIED_BACKUP/backup_20250503_003105.tar.gz -C /home/ubuntu/CAPS/RESTORED_DATA

4. Move the restored file to the main System's docker-data location
    NOTE: backup the existing docker-data folder if necessary.
    To backup, run below command

    mv /home/ubuntu/CAPS/docker-data /home/ubuntu/CAPS/docker-data_<BACKUP_NAME>

   # Move the restored data
   mv /home/ubuntu/CAPS/RESTORED_DATA/docker-data/ /home/ubuntu/CAPS/

5. Validate  

ls -lht /home/ubuntu/CAPS/docker-data
total 8.0K
drwxr-xr-x 8 ubuntu ubuntu 4.0K May  2 23:43 mysql_data
drwxrwxr-x 4 ubuntu ubuntu 4.0K Apr 29 17:00 backend_pictures


6. Start the containers

cd <PROJECT_DIRECTORY>
    docker-compose start

7. Confirmed if data have been restored successfully by navigating the system.